==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dionysia
<hw>Di`o*ny"si*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
Gr. <?/.]</ety> <fld>(Class. Antiq.)</fld> <def>Any of the festivals
held in honor of the Olympian god Dionysus. They correspond to the Roman
Bacchanalia; the greater Dionysia were held at Athens in March or April,
and were celebrated with elaborate performances of both tragedies and
comedies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dionysiac</ent>⟦br⟧
